K-means Animation function

Ganbold, MungunSarnai

9/12/2019

Optional working extension to the ‘hw1_Ganbold_Mungunsarnai.rmd’:

Clustering and vizualizing with kmeans.ani(), k=2:

data(iris)
iris_clust <- as.data.frame(iris[,-5])

#install.packages("animation")
set.seed(2345)
library(animation)
clusters_2 <- kmeans.ani(iris_clust[2:3], 2)

str(clusters_2)
## List of 2
##  $ cluster: int [1:150] 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 ...
##  $ centers: num [1:2, 1:2] 2.88 3.41 4.93 1.49
##   ..- attr(*, "dimnames")=List of 2
##   .. ..$ : NULL
##   .. ..$ : chr [1:2] "Sepal.Width" "Petal.Length"

k-means animation with k=4:

#install.packages("animation")
set.seed(2345)
library(animation)
kmeans.ani(iris_clust[2:3], 4)
